<br>
LEar: Forest Loop<br>
Neck:Chrysoberyl Talisman<br>
Face:Plat Ruby Veil<br>
Head: Nightshade Wreath<br>
REar:Golden Jasper<br>
<br>
LFinger:Velium Jasper Ring<br>
RFinger:  Plat Jasper Ring<br>
RWrist: Runed Mithril Bracer<br>
LWrist:  Supple Scale Armband<br>
Gloves: Split Paw Hide gloves<br>
<br>
Shoulders:  Braided Ivy Cords<br>
Chest:Mithril-Runed Tunic<br>
Back: Kunzar Cloak<br>
Legs: Kromriff Military Leggings<br>
Waist:Crystalline Belt<br>
Feet: Imbued Vale Studded Boots <br>
<br>
RHand: Nature Walkers Scimitar<br>
LHand: Testament of Vaneer<br>
Range: Throwing Hammers<br>
Ammo: Throwing Hammers<br>
<br>
Have about 2k.  Need to know if I need to get more money to buy stuff or if I should just go and start looking for good trades ?  Where I should hunt to get the armor ?  Any help would be GREATLY appreciated.  <br>
<br>
Thank you, <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukiatek2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kiatek2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/13/01 6:04:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another help on Armor, sorry</span><hr size=1> would be a little helpful if you had listed level, wis, etc.  here are a few suggestions (based on you being 50+):<br>
<br>
Face:  if possible find a group doing fire giants, get a polished mithril mask.  5 ac 7 wis/int-same wis but add ac-free<br>
<br>
Face:  Enshrouded Veil-dont remember stats but has nice hp/mana-high price though 2000ish pp or comes from howling stones.<br>
<br>
Head:  Get crown of froglok kings-approx 800 pp if you see for sale or get group and go there for free-12 ac 20 fire/cold (my opinion and no offense intended but wreath is junk-ac and resists were more impt to me than 5 wis)<br>
<br>
Gloves:  Gem Inlaid guantlets-quest getting the scrolls from gnolls in SK and splitpaw-free or pay 200 pp-8 ac some other stats dont remember-add ac over a little wis and regular chain look<br>
<br>
Gloves:  Elder Spriritist Guantlets-1000 to 1500 pp-9 ac effect snare-once again lost wis but gain ac and nice effect and nice dark green chain look if you are into that<br>
<br>
Gloves:  minor upgrade to split paw is gnome skin.  few more ac and one more wis maybe, dont remember.<br>
<br>
Shoulders:  start shawl quests (thurgadin quest series) if you have velious and have faction-quests one through four are fairly simply and dont require alot of time investment.  quest five is better than cords but requires alot of time invested in tailoring.  dont start if you dont want to spend some time in tradeskills.<br>
<br>
Shoulders:  Tattered Mantle 12 ac 10 dis? 20 hp- more ac with some hp-cheap 100 pp or less<br>
<br>
Chest:  Shroud of Nature 13 ac 6 wis 8 sv fire/cold-sells for 1Kish at most or go to droga and get one-threads in various places about camping this one<br>
<br>
Back:  Mammoth Hide Cloak  7 ac 4 wis 10 sv cold-add 2 wis.  goes for about 1K now or go to Permafrost and camp it (boring *yawn* but doable)<br>
<br>
LHand:  Charred Guardian Shield 9 ac 9 wis- no holds barred major improvement over testament in my opinion-add alot of ac and only lost 1 wis and 10 mana.  300 pp max or go to sol A and get it off the EXG clockwork-magic resistant little bugger though so be prepared for that.<br>
<br>
Range:  Work pottery a little and make small wis diety-2 wis or small resist diety-dont remember stats or simply buy them-they sell for less than 100 pp.  Pottery is EASY to get up to 130ish-takes less than 50 pp and about two hours.<br>
<br>
<br>
This will take 2 wis off your total but add 40 to 50 raw ac which is a significant gain as well as some other stats and nice resists.  Only listed the affordable stuff and stuff that came to my mind right away.  <br>
<br>
There are tons of other things i am sure others might list-for instance Golden Efreeti Boots-5ac 7 wis/int (or is it 9-i forget) but these cost around 6K now-you could get a group and get some though.  you can also keep a couple sets of gear: one for high high wis/mana for kiting/soloing and one for grouping with a little more ac and resists.  Good luck.<br>
